						h1 A-Frame facts
						p Framework on top of Three.JS
						p Open-source, version 0.7.0 as of Sept. 27th, 2017.
						p.fragment Focus on virtual reality experiences.
						p.fragment Still good for AR, general 3D interactives
					section.vertical-slide
						h1 How A-Frame works
					section.vertical-slide
						h1 HTML5 Custom elements
						p.fragment Allow you to write HTML-like syntax for 3D objects on the web.
						p.fragment Can use stadard DOM selection APIs like #[code document.querySelector] (or jQuery!) to manipulate 3D objects
					section.vertical-slide
						h1 Example (360 video):
						pre
							code
								| &lt;a-scene&gt;

								|   &lt;a-assets&gt;

								|     &lt;video id="video-texture" src="assets/test-video.mp4" autoplay muted crossorigin="anonymous" playsinline -webkit-playsinline&gt;&lt;/video&gt;

								|   &lt;/a-assets&gt;

								|   &lt;a-videosphere src="#video-texture" rotation="0 255 0"&gt;&lt;/a-videosphere&gt;

								| &lt;/a-scene&gt;
					section(class="vertical-slide credited-section" data-background-iframe="https://aframe.io/aframe/examples/boilerplate/360-video/")
